casebody.data:
PEOPLE ex rel. FITZGERALD v. WOODS, Police Com’r. (No. 368.) (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. May 28, 1915.) Mandamus by the People, on relation of William J. Fitzgerald, against Arthur Woods, as Police Commissioner of the City of New York. From an order granting a peremptory writ, defendant appeals. Reversed, and motion for writ denied.

Argued before JENKS, P. J., and THOMAS, CARR, RICH, and PUTNAM, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Order reversed, with $10 costs and disbursements, and relator's motion denied, with $25 costs. See opinion in People ex rel. Walter v. Woods, 153 N. Y. Supp. 872, decided herewith.
